Reasoning: The paper discusses the creation of artificial intelligence in financial markets, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed test for intelligence in trading programs is similar to the Turing Test, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for guiding principles and decision-making in AI, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also touches upon the ethical considerations of AI in finance, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
